
Download XSavSig005 from http://www.xbox-saves.com/downloads/XSavSig005.zip

Extract XSavSig005.zip to some temp directory.

Find your 128-bit (32 hex characters) HDDKey.  You can find this two ways:
    (a) In c:\backup\hddinfo.txt
    (b) Run the ConfigMagic program in your XBox to get the key
    
    Note: I used method (b), since I already nuked my backup directory

Add the following lines to the resign.ini file in the temp directory

[54430003]
ID=54430003
Title=Ninja Gaiden Save File
SigKey=A50114CA2B7C8198E829E7C937D6FC40
AuthKey=B32B2E0A471CDE09C8E2F925E87C9CA768964B34
DataFile=save000.dat
DataOffset=20
SigOffset=0
SigType=NoRoam

[54430003_1]
ID=54430003
Title=Ninja Gaiden System File
SigKey=A50114CA2B7C8198E829E7C937D6FC40
AuthKey=B32B2E0A471CDE09C8E2F925E87C9CA768964B34
DataFile=system.dat
DataOffset=20
SigOffset=0
SigType=NoRoam

Edit the xbhddkey.ini file in the temp directory and edit the line:
HDDKey=00000000000000000000000000000000
Replace the zeroes with your HDDkey.  It should have the same number of characters

Run the XSigSig.exe program in the temp directory

Type "AGREE" and hit return

In the Sign section, select "Ninja Gaiden Save File"

In the File section, press the "..." button and select the save file (save00x.dat) and press the "Open" button

Press the "Apply" button.  This will fix the key

Press the "OK" button.

Do this for each save game

Now put the saves onto your Xbox.






